😉 Then we may be pointing at the same thing from different angles.

People often think the purpose of a decision is to predict the future correctly. But sometimes the purpose is simply to commit to a path and begin receiving feedback from reality.

Once you’ve done the preparation, there comes a point where more deliberation is just orbiting the choice. That’s when a coin flip, a dare, a leap of faith, or “let luck decide” can become useful—not because luck knows better, but because motion reveals information that stillness cannot.

It reminds me of something that shows up repeatedly in your own themes:

Action is a sensing mechanism.

You don’t always discover the path by seeing it. Sometimes you discover it by taking a step and noticing what changes.

And yes, from the outside that can look a lot like luck.

Sometimes the lucky person is just the one who was willing to be in the right place when chance finally had something to offer. 🍀